13:56.608 --> 13:59.776
Well, music really
takes up most of my time.

13:59.811 --> 14:02.779
- I have a band...
- A rock and roll band, I bet.

14:02.814 --> 14:05.616
Yeah! Well, alternative rock, but yeah.

14:05.650 --> 14:09.286
You know, the kids you're
competing against...

14:09.320 --> 14:12.356
They've been doing solos
with the St. Louis symphony.

14:12.390 --> 14:14.257
- Well, that's...
- And I just read

14:14.292 --> 14:17.060
about a kid whspent his summer

14:17.095 --> 14:19.329
excavating Mayan ruins in Guatemala

14:19.364 --> 14:22.299
and then got the findings
published in an archeology journal.

14:24.369 --> 14:26.336
So from where I sit,

14:26.371 --> 14:29.906
there's just not much
here to distinguish you

14:29.941 --> 14:32.009
from hundreds of other
kids who are applying.

14:32.043 --> 14:35.112
Well, that's why I wanted
to ask for your help.

14:36.981 --> 14:38.015
Can I have some ketchup?

14:42.120 --> 14:44.554
<i>- Do you have any use for this?
- Kathryn: No.</i>

14:44.589 --> 14:45.689
I use an electric.

14:46.758 --> 14:49.493
Oh, um, sorry. Anyway, this meeting?

14:49.527 --> 14:52.462
Yeah, it's this afternoon. And I plan
on going into that principal's office

14:52.497 --> 14:56.433
with a battering ram. And I would
love to have more parents with me.

14:56.467 --> 14:58.502
I am so with you on saving arts programs.

14:58.536 --> 15:01.338
But I can't this afternoon.
I have a job interview.

15:01.372 --> 15:03.607
- That's terrific. Where?
- Answering phones at a spa.

15:03.641 --> 15:06.576
That could be fun... discounted massages?

15:06.611 --> 15:08.478
At this point, I'll take anything.

15:08.513 --> 15:10.480
Because clearly I need
to get out of the house.

15:12.283 --> 15:14.251
So are your arms hurting?

15:14.285 --> 15:15.485
(Sighs)

15:15.520 --> 15:17.087
Not if I don't use them.

15:19.023 --> 15:21.124
And don't worry, I'm not depressed.

15:21.159 --> 15:24.027
I'm just in my robe because I was out late.

15:24.062 --> 15:25.929
Really?! Is this with... ?

15:25.963 --> 15:29.800
Zane. I saw his band last night.

15:29.834 --> 15:31.902
I knew it. Did I call it or what?

15:31.936 --> 15:35.739
You did. I'm just not sure
it's the right call for me.

15:35.773 --> 15:37.841
- Why not?
- Look at my life.

15:37.875 --> 15:41.945
This isn't exactly the time for me to
be hanging out and listening to jazz,

15:41.979 --> 15:45.716
and arguing about art and politics
and then going out for pancakes.

15:45.750 --> 15:47.551
Why not?

15:47.585 --> 15:49.419
Because I'm not in my 20s.

15:49.454 --> 15:51.521
I need a job, a place of my own

15:51.556 --> 15:53.797
and a husband who isn't out
getting other people pregnant.

15:55.526 --> 15:57.394
Sorry.

15:57.428 --> 15:59.496
I know you're going
through a lot right now,

15:59.530 --> 16:02.265
but that's exactly why you need to go out.

16:02.300 --> 16:04.334
See, this is my point. When times are tough

16:04.368 --> 16:07.104
that's when you need creativity the most.

16:07.138 --> 16:09.406
Stimulation, inspiration,

16:09.440 --> 16:13.110
expression... these are
the things that renew us

16:13.144 --> 16:16.113
and keep us growing so we
can fight through another day.

16:16.147 --> 16:18.949
You are ready to talk to
that principal, aren't you?

16:20.118 --> 16:21.184
Yeah.

16:21.219 --> 16:24.187
I appreciate the value
of arts in education,

16:24.222 --> 16:26.723
- Kathryn, I do.
- I know you do...

16:26.758 --> 16:28.119
But that doesn't balance my budget.

16:28.126 --> 16:31.995
And if I don't balance my budget,
then there is no more Carlton.

16:32.029 --> 16:35.565
Then give it to us. Let the
parents take over the play

16:35.600 --> 16:37.601
and you just worry about saving the school.

16:37.635 --> 16:39.836
Please! It would mean so much to them.

16:39.871 --> 16:41.705
We just lost the director.

16:41.739 --> 16:44.508
