17:41.532 --> 17:42.666
Yeah.

17:42.700 --> 17:45.302
- Is he throwing gang signs at you?
- No no,

17:45.336 --> 17:47.671
- it's sign language. We're deaf.
- For real?

17:47.705 --> 17:50.340
- But you heard what I said.
- I read your lips.

17:50.374 --> 17:51.474
Cool.

17:51.509 --> 17:54.110
Who do you work for? I've
never seen this truck before.

17:54.145 --> 17:55.512
- Oh, it's mine.
- Yours?

17:55.546 --> 17:57.247
- Mm-hmm.
- Damn.

17:57.281 --> 18:00.016
I can hear and see perfect...
all I got is an old bike.

18:00.051 --> 18:01.384
(Laughs)

18:03.287 --> 18:05.288
Hey, you know what you
should do? Put your picture

18:05.323 --> 18:07.958
on the side of the truck,
call it "deaf hot tacos."

18:07.992 --> 18:10.927
With a face like yours, guys will
be lining up around the block.

18:10.962 --> 18:13.096
Thanks. Enjoy.

18:18.777 --> 18:21.212
_

18:22.707 --> 18:25.675
Ooh, scary.

18:25.710 --> 18:27.043
I'm sorry about the mess.

18:27.078 --> 18:28.945
I promise I'm going to clean it up.

18:28.980 --> 18:32.515
No, it's fine. It's nice
having you work here.

18:34.518 --> 18:36.887
I hate to bother you
while you're in "the zone,"

18:36.921 --> 18:38.788
but I just wanted to tell you

18:38.823 --> 18:41.491
that some wonderfully
committed Carlton parent

18:41.525 --> 18:43.526
spoke to principal rose this afternoon

18:43.561 --> 18:46.429
and it looks like the play is back on.

18:46.464 --> 18:49.466
- Seriously? Who did that?
- Me.

18:49.500 --> 18:52.235
That's amazing! Thank you.

18:52.270 --> 18:54.404
Rehearsals start tomorrow after school,

18:54.438 --> 18:56.273
and I am so excited!

18:56.307 --> 18:59.042
Why are you so excited?

18:59.076 --> 19:03.179
Well, as you know, they had to
cut the salary of the director

19:03.214 --> 19:06.216
because of the budget, so it
became a volunteer position.

19:06.250 --> 19:09.052
- You volunteered.
- Yeah.

19:09.086 --> 19:10.987
It's just a stopgap measure.

19:11.022 --> 19:14.824
Are you really qualified
to do something like this?

19:14.859 --> 19:17.961
I've been in a lot of plays and I directed
the holiday pageant at the church...

19:17.995 --> 19:20.764
Right, uh... yeah, I know.

19:21.933 --> 19:23.733
I'm sure it's gonna be fine.

19:25.536 --> 19:28.438
Hey, how did it go with your grandfather?

19:29.540 --> 19:30.807
Uh, actually not so good.

19:30.841 --> 19:33.643
What do you mean? Is he going
to make the call or what?

19:33.678 --> 19:36.446
I don't know. He didn't say.

19:36.480 --> 19:39.616
Huh. So what did he say?

19:39.650 --> 19:42.452
That I am not Wash U material.

19:42.486 --> 19:47.157
- He said that?
- Well yeah, that I'm...

19:47.191 --> 19:49.392
Like everybody else that's applying.

19:49.427 --> 19:51.428
Did you tell him about your music?

19:51.462 --> 19:55.198
I tried, but he just
kept calling it a hobby.

19:55.232 --> 19:57.167
Honestly, I don't even care.

19:57.201 --> 19:59.069
Okay, you know what? Listen to me.

19:59.103 --> 20:01.338
Your music, your band... these are things

20:01.372 --> 20:03.907
that are going to set
your application apart.

20:03.941 --> 20:05.075
And your grandfather...

20:08.746 --> 20:10.747
(Clears throat) he's not the kind of man

20:10.781 --> 20:12.048
to offer a lot of approval.

20:12.083 --> 20:14.651
He's got his own ideas

20:14.685 --> 20:16.553
about how things should go.

20:16.587 --> 20:19.622
And if you want to go your
own way... like, let's say,

20:19.657 --> 20:22.692
turn down a football scholarship
to the University of Iowa

20:22.727 --> 20:24.661
to play baseball in the major leagues...

20:24.695 --> 20:26.730
no amount of success

20:26.764 --> 20:28.531
will make him come around.

20:28.566 --> 20:30.700
All he sees

20:30.735 --> 20:33.269
is that you didn't do it his way.

20:36.440 --> 20:39.376
Well, if I did it his way, I'd
better start high school again.

20:39.410 --> 20:41.244
Now you listen to me.

20:41.278 --> 20:43.980
This afternoon, you
put it out of your head.

20:44.015 --> 20:47.984
You finish those applications.
He does not get to derail you.

20:48.019 --> 20:50.887
- But, dad, I...
- No buts, Toby.

20:50.921 --> 20:53.289
You get those applications in.

21:01.903 --> 21:03.137
So, what was the theory again?

21:04.112 --> 21:06.313
Family connections are gonna
help Toby get into college?

21:06.348 --> 21:08.282
- Did he talk to your dad?
- Oh yeah.

21:08.316 --> 21:11.251
Just long enough to start thinking
he doesn't have a shot at getting in.

21:11.286 --> 21:14.855
- How did he do that?
- I know exactly how he did it.

21:17.192 --> 21:20.794
Peering over his glasses like
you both know it's the truth,

21:20.829 --> 21:23.063
and if you can't admit it, you're a coward.

21:23.098 --> 21:25.165
Okay,

21:25.200 --> 21:27.134
we know Toby.

21:27.168 --> 21:31.038
He may get pushed off
his axis for a day or two,

21:31.072 --> 21:32.806
but he'll think about it

21:32.841 --> 21:34.775
and he'll come back stronger than ever.

21:34.809 --> 21:37.644
- You sure about that?
- He's not like you, John.

21:37.679 --> 21:39.880
- What's that supposed to mean?
- It means he didn't grow up

21:39.948 --> 21:42.383
having to defend himself all the time.

21:42.417 --> 21:45.386
He has a loving father

21:45.420 --> 21:47.388
who supports him. He'll take it in

21:47.422 --> 21:49.656
and then remember who is.

21:51.259 --> 21:53.260
Reggie, come on, it's
not even midnight yet.

21:53.294 --> 21:55.262
What, is your car gonna
turn into a pumpkin?

21:55.296 --> 21:57.297
Have you seen my car? Because
that would be an improvement.

21:57.332 --> 22:01.135
Okay, have you had the
Martinis at the green mill?

22:01.169 --> 22:04.104
- Because if you haven't...
- Zane, I gotta get home.

22:04.139 --> 22:06.440
Do you understand?
Responsibility, daughter,

22:06.474 --> 22:10.177
- crappy jobs to apply for.
- All of which will still be there

22:10.211 --> 22:12.312
- after the Martini.
- (Laughs)

22:12.347 --> 22:15.249
<i>Have you even had a day job?</i>

22:15.283 --> 22:17.151
Uh, hell yes.

22:17.185 --> 22:20.187
Reupholstering furniture in my
Uncle's shop. I was miserable.

22:20.221 --> 22:22.990
By the way, it's not like I'm
living a life of leisure here.

22:23.024 --> 22:25.092
But it's a hell of a lot more fun.

22:26.928 --> 22:28.028
(Sighs)

22:28.062 --> 22:30.063
You know what?

22:31.966 --> 22:35.068
Maybe I'm just not in a fun
place in my life right now.

22:35.103 --> 22:36.970
Uh-oh.

22:37.005 --> 22:39.473
You live in Oz,

22:39.507 --> 22:41.809
and I am in Kansas

22:41.843 --> 22:44.611
in, like, the middle of a tornado.

22:44.646 --> 22:47.581
- Hold on...
- And honestly? I don't even like jazz all that much.

22:47.615 --> 22:49.616
(Chuckles)

22:49.651 --> 22:51.585
There she is.

22:51.619 --> 22:54.254
There's the girl I remember.

22:54.289 --> 22:56.423
I think she is long gone.

22:56.458 --> 22:58.459
You don't think I haven't changed either?

22:58.493 --> 23:01.361
I have two grown girls. I have an ex-wife.

23:01.396 --> 23:04.097
I'm putting together gigs week to week.

23:04.132 --> 23:06.099
I know.

23:07.302 --> 23:09.903
And I really like hanging out with you.

23:09.938 --> 23:11.839
But...

23:11.873 --> 23:13.907
I gotta deal with the tornado.

23:22.784 --> 23:24.084
(Sighs)

23:28.756 --> 23:30.624
Take care of yourself.

23:50.245 --> 23:52.079
(Exhales)

24:33.855 --> 24:36.456
- Hey there.
- Damn, those tacos were good.

24:36.491 --> 24:38.625
- Thanks.
- What do you put in them?

24:38.660 --> 24:40.360
My secret ingredient.

24:40.395 --> 24:43.263
Hey, how do you say
"taco" in sign language?

24:43.298 --> 24:45.332
Just how it looks... like this.

24:45.366 --> 24:47.134
That's cool.

24:47.168 --> 24:49.169
- What's your name?
- Daphne.

24:49.203 --> 24:51.371
So, Daphne,

24:51.406 --> 24:53.273
you wanna go out sometime?

24:55.043 --> 24:56.209
<i>(Faint rattling)</i>

24:56.244 --> 24:57.911
Uh...

25:00.214 --> 25:01.815
