38:07.421 --> 38:09.255
Hey. So,

38:09.289 --> 38:11.223
I have been in touch with Darryl,

38:11.258 --> 38:13.392
my old batting coach with the
Royals. He's a Wash U alum.

38:13.427 --> 38:16.062
Turns out his brother is a Dean over there.

38:16.096 --> 38:18.264
<i>He wants to sit down with
you and call his brother</i>

38:18.298 --> 38:20.199
who's got a little pull.

38:20.233 --> 38:23.002
- Oh.
- C'mon! This is great news.

38:23.036 --> 38:25.738
Yeah, it's just...

38:25.772 --> 38:27.740
I don't know. I've been thinking.

38:27.774 --> 38:30.943
I only applied to Wash U because
my counselor said I should.

38:30.978 --> 38:34.680
- If you don't want to go there...
- Any college really.

38:34.715 --> 38:38.718
I mean I only applied because
that's what you're supposed to do...

38:38.752 --> 38:41.721
Ah, no no. It's about growing up

38:41.755 --> 38:43.489
and starting life as an adult.

38:43.523 --> 38:45.658
But college isn't the only way to do that.

38:45.692 --> 38:47.827
You said you never grew
up faster than that summer

38:47.861 --> 38:51.430
you played baseball for that
Cape COD league when you were 17.

38:51.465 --> 38:54.667
- I was on a different path.
- I don't even know if I have a path.

38:54.701 --> 38:56.569
See that right there?

38:56.603 --> 38:59.538
That is exactly what
your grandfather wanted:

38:59.573 --> 39:02.608
get under your skin and
make you doubt yourself.

39:02.642 --> 39:05.478
Dad, this isn't about you
and grandpa and who's right.

39:05.512 --> 39:08.180
It's about me and what I want.

39:08.215 --> 39:11.183
You know what, it's okay to
be nervous or even have doubts.

39:11.218 --> 39:13.252
College is a big change,

39:13.286 --> 39:16.055
but you have the entire
summer ahead of you.

39:16.089 --> 39:18.124
Do what you want...

39:18.158 --> 39:20.393
travel, play music, loaf around.

39:20.427 --> 39:22.928
No pressure.

39:22.963 --> 39:25.231
You do not have to make
up your mind right now.

39:27.000 --> 39:28.968
Well, I have made up my mind.

39:30.037 --> 39:31.904
I'm not going to college next year.

39:36.276 --> 39:39.712
Hey. So did you do

39:39.746 --> 39:41.781
a set design idea?

39:42.568 --> 39:45.063
_

39:45.752 --> 39:46.852
Oh.

39:46.853 --> 39:48.810
_

39:48.922 --> 39:51.624
No, I get it.

40:01.535 --> 40:04.370
We have a pretty serious situation here.

40:04.404 --> 40:08.574
The school has no money
for any of this... nothing.

40:08.608 --> 40:11.644
Not for sets, not for costumes,

40:11.678 --> 40:13.579
not for interpreters

40:13.613 --> 40:16.315
and definitely not for drama teachers.

40:17.517 --> 40:20.186
So we need to be doing this,

40:20.220 --> 40:23.055
all of us,

40:23.090 --> 40:25.224
solely out of love.

40:27.127 --> 40:29.228
Love for the theater,

40:29.262 --> 40:33.132
and love for working together as a team...

40:33.166 --> 40:35.935
each of us with different talents

40:35.969 --> 40:38.237
and different ideas, coming together

40:38.271 --> 40:41.207
to create something that just might be...

40:43.076 --> 40:44.877
great.

40:46.246 --> 40:49.982
So if you're ready to do this with me,

40:50.016 --> 40:52.818
then stay. And if you're not,

40:52.853 --> 40:54.153
then it's time to go.

41:05.832 --> 41:08.567
Good. Then let's get started.

41:08.602 --> 41:11.504
I've made some copies
of the opening scene...

41:12.572 --> 41:13.906
and here you go.

41:25.519 --> 41:28.754
<i>- Zane: Hey.
- Did I miss your whole set?</i>

41:28.788 --> 41:30.623
Perfect timing actually.

41:30.657 --> 41:32.725
We were just about to
go get something to eat.

41:32.759 --> 41:34.894
You guys go. I'm not that hungry.

41:34.928 --> 41:36.829
<i>Bartender: Aw man, jackpot!</i>

41:36.863 --> 41:39.632
Somebody left like half a Bordeaux.

41:39.666 --> 41:41.600
It's a $300 bottle, people.

41:41.635 --> 41:43.702
- Who's in?
- Can't pass that up.

41:43.737 --> 41:45.571
Regina?

41:49.876 --> 41:52.912
You know, you look fantastic tonight.

41:52.946 --> 41:55.481
<i>Where are you guys headed?</i>

41:56.716 --> 41:59.585
Uh, Emerald City.

41:59.619 --> 42:03.789
<i>* it's just a vacation... *</i>

42:06.893 --> 42:09.862
<i>- bartender: Nice, right?
- Beautiful.</i>

42:09.896 --> 42:11.797
Guess you're done with that cleanse.

42:11.831 --> 42:14.867
All done.

42:14.901 --> 42:17.536
So, Regina, what do you do?

42:17.571 --> 42:19.772
Cosmetology for a lot of years,

42:19.806 --> 42:23.609
but I'm open to something new right now.

42:23.643 --> 42:24.643
Regina came here

42:24.678 --> 42:26.545
ever since T.J. was running it.

42:26.580 --> 42:29.748
- No.
- (Regina chuckles)

42:29.783 --> 42:31.850
You're the one that can dance, right?

42:31.918 --> 42:34.553
- Oh, she can?
- I've heard of her!

42:34.588 --> 42:36.555
(Conversation fades)

